    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{-18, 7, 8, 7, -17, 13, 13, 21, -9\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the sample mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1}{n} \\sum_{i=1}^{n} x_i\n$$\n\nWhere $ n = 9 $, and the data is:\n\n$$\n-18, 7, 8, 7, -17, 13, 13, 21, -9\n$$\n\nSum the values:\n\n$$\n-18 + 7 + 8 + 7 - 17 + 13 + 13 + 21 - 9 = 15\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{15}{9} = \\frac{5}{3}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n(x_i - \\bar{x})^2\n$$\n\nLet's compute each term:\n\n| $ x_i $ | $ x_i - \\bar{x} $ | $ (x_i - \\bar{x})^2 $ |\n|----------|---------------------|--------------------------|\n| -18      | -18 - 5/3 = -59/3   | $ \\left(-\\frac{59}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{3481}{9} $ |\n| 7        | 7 - 5/3 = 16/3      | $ \\left(\\frac{16}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{256}{9} $ |\n| 8        | 8 - 5/3 = 23/3      | $ \\left(\\frac{23}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{529}{9} $ |\n| 7        | 7 - 5/3 = 16/3      | $ \\frac{256}{9} $ |\n| -17      | -17 - 5/3 = -56/3   | $ \\left(-\\frac{56}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{3136}{9} $ |\n| 1"
